bug.short_desc: No PDF and TIFF export in djview4
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1222363 Djvu file to test.
Description of problem: Program doesn't let to export ".djvu" file as ".pdf" file or ".tiff" images since there is no such menu items in drop-down menu.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): Name : djview4 Arch : x86_64 Epoch : 0 Version : 4.10.6 Release : 3.fc24 Size : 1.8 M Repo : @System From repo : updates Summary : DjVu viewer URL : http://djvu.sourceforge.net/djview4.html License : GPLv2+
How reproducible: No menu items in drop-down menu. They should be placed there because pdf or tiff conversion is one of the most important features of this piece of software.
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Start djview4 2. Open any ".djvu" file or attached "example.djvu". 3. Go to "File > Export as..." 4. In the "Export" tab in "Destination" section choose "Format:" by opening drop-down menu. 5. There should be "PDF Document" and "TIFF image" items in addition to existing ones but they dont exist.
Actual results: No results!
Expected results: Pdf conversion from ".djvu" files.
Additional info: This bug affects only djview4 from Fedora repository. This program exports files as it supposed to on any other distros like ubuntu or debian.
I guess PDF support completely depends on TIFF. Adding BRs should enable it.
